<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,158,401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,465,158,184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="178">Taxonomic remarks:—</emphasis>
The salmon-coloured basidioma makes this a conspicuous species when observed in the field. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schwein. ex Fr.) Rajchenb." authorityName="Rajchenb." baseAuthorityName="Fr." box="[202,709,194,221]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="2" pageNumber="178" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="spissa">
<emphasis box="[202,387,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="178">Ceriporia spissa</emphasis>
(Schwein. ex Fr.) Rajchenb.
</taxonomicName>
has a similar color, but it has pores ranging from 7−9 per mm and allantoid basidiospores (
<bibRefCitation author="Aime, L. &amp; Ryvarden, L. &amp; Henkel, T. W." box="[405,596,230,256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="178" pagination="15 - 31" refId="ref2551" refString="Aime, L., Ryvarden, L. &amp; Henkel, T. W. (2007) Studies in Neotropical polypores 22. Additional new and rare species from Guyana. Synopsis Fungorum 23: 15 - 31." type="journal article" year="2007">
Aime 
<emphasis box="[475,530,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="178">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, the basidiospores of 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1125,231,257]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="2" pageNumber="178" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="amazonica">
<emphasis box="[973,1125,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="178">C. amazonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are among the smallest in the genus and should aid in the identification of the species. 
<taxonomicName authority="M. Mata &amp; Ryvarden" authorityName="M. Mata &amp; Ryvarden" box="[764,1239,266,293]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="2" pageNumber="178" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="incrustata">
<emphasis box="[764,995,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="178">Ceriporia incrustata</emphasis>
M. Mata &amp; Ryvarden
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="I. Lindblad &amp; Ryvarden" authorityName="I. Lindblad &amp; Ryvarden" authorityYear="1999" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="2" pageNumber="178" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="microspora">
<emphasis box="[1291,1451,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="178">C. microspora</emphasis>
I. Lindblad &amp; Ryvarden
</taxonomicName>
have basidiospores of similar size (3−3.5 × 1.8−2 μm and 3−3.5 × 1.5−2 μm, respectively), but smaller pores (6−8 per mm in both species). Besides, the former has ochraceous basidiomata and the latter, white basidiomata (
<bibRefCitation author="Lindblad, I. &amp; Ryvarden, L." box="[286,598,374,400]" pageId="2" pageNumber="178" pagination="335 - 359" refId="ref2921" refString="Lindblad, I. &amp; Ryvarden, L. (1999) Studies in neotropical polypores. 3. New and interesting Basidiomycetes (Poriales) from Costa Rica. Mycotaxon 71: 335 - 359." type="journal article" year="1999">Lindblad &amp; Ryvarden 1999</bibRefCitation>
, Mata &amp; Ryvarden 2010).
</paragraph>
